---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';import receipt from '../../../benchmarks/shootout/languages/latest.json';
const rows=receipt.results;
---
<Layout title="Engine language shootout"><header><p class="eyebrow">Compiler Shootout v1 · Axis A</p><h1>Engine language: no supported winner</h1><p>This is a planner-only comparison. Correctness passed for all four engines, but every product gate is blocked. CPU and peak RSS are blocked, so wall samples cannot support an implementation winner.</p></header><section><h2>Separate Axis A verdict</h2><dl><div><dt>Selected records</dt><dd>8 exact records (4 languages × Button and Select)</dd></div><div><dt>Scope</dt><dd>Planner correctness, performance and distribution</dd></div><div><dt>Winner supported?</dt><dd><strong>No</strong></dd></div></dl></section><section><h2>Planner results</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Engine</th><th>Correctness</th><th>Samples</th><th>CPU / RSS</th><th>Product gates</th></tr></thead><tbody>{rows.map(r=><tr><td>{r.language}</td><td>{r.correctness}</td><td>{r.performance.samples.length} wall samples</td><td>blocked / blocked</td><td>all blocked</td></tr>)}</tbody></table><p class="caveat">Evidence caveat: deterministic planner artifacts are not framework emitters, browser parity, package readiness, or the immutable 164/164 baseline authority.</p><p><a href="/receipts/shootout-language.json">Drill down to the selected Axis A receipt →</a></p></section></Layout>
<style>header,section{max-width:900px;margin:35px auto}.eyebrow{color:#64748b;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:700}h1{font-size:45px}p{line-height:1.6}dl{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:12px}dl div,.caveat{padding:16px;background:#f1f5f9;border-radius:8px}dt{font-size:12px;color:#64748b}dd{margin:8px 0 0}table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse}th,td{text-align:left;padding:12px;border-bottom:1px solid #ddd}@media(max-width:700px){dl{grid-template-columns:1fr}table{font-size:12px}}</style>
